Vol / Page:  C2
Edition:
Quote:  On June 26, 1958, Minister of Finance Arnold Nordmeyer presented his first budget. It has gone down in political history as the "black budget" and it helped consign its author to political purgatory... In a statement issued on the night of the budget speech the two presidents of the North and South Island Motor Unions called it "black Thursday" and Federation of Labour strongman Fintan Patrick Walsh was soon labelling it the "black budget".
